description: Stop by the Scarlet Arts Rx table at the Art Library (facing the Voorhees Mall lawn) to learn about both of us! Scarlet Arts Rx is funded by the RU-NB Chancellor's Office and is brought to you by two Rutgers schools - Mason Gross School of the Arts (MGSA) and Graduate School of Applied and Professional Psychology (GSAPP) (https://go.rutgers.edu/ScarletWell-ScarletArtsRx)! The Art Library is an amazing resource (https://libguides.rutgers.edu/artlibrary) and is planning to hand out fresh, hot popcorn! Can't wait to meet you! >>>>>>   Discover the transformative power of the arts through a FREE arts and well-being program for all Rutgers-New Brunswick students called Scarlet Arts Rx!Did you know that arts engagement is related to improvements in:• Positive mood (less anxiety/stress)• Sleep quality (linked to better academic performance)• Social connections• Self-confidence• Creative thinking skills, and more?   Students from every major can benefit. You don’t need to be an artist!What will I get?>> Free, reserved Mason Gross School of The Arts (MGSA) box office tickets for theater, dance, and music performances while supplies last>> Recommendations of free arts activities/events we think you may enjoy >> When you fill out a 1-minute feedback survey after each arts activity/event you attend or do, you’ll be entered into a monthly drawing for a chance to win a $50 gift card.>> Opportunities to connect socially through group and self-guided activities!After you sign up using this 2-minute form, we’ll contact you to connect you with arts activities/events: https://go.rutgers.edu/ScarletArtsSignUp
name: Scarlet Arts Rx Tabling at the Art Library
organizationName: Scarlet Arts Rx (Affiliated with a Mason Gross School of the Arts Department)

description: We hope you’re having a great start to your semester! We are Anakbayan Rutgers, an on-campus chapter of a mass organization of youth and students fighting to address the struggles of Filipinos – in the Philippines and abroad. We aim to inform others about political issues happening in the Philippines, and engage with members of the local Filipino Community. But most importantly we strive to educate, organize, and mobilize the community, starting right here at Rutgers, to fight towards achieving genuine democracy and freedom. Join us after the Involvement Fair (date tbd), to not only be given a chance to learn more about Anakbayan but also an opportunity for us to become more engaged in the Rutgers community. We hope that you will join us for all the food and fun activities we will be having for this open house, and we look forward to meeting you!
name: Anakbayan Open House Fall 2024

description: Scarlet Game Jam is a biannual game jam hosted by the Creation of Games Society at Rutgers University. Similar to any other game jam, participants will be given one week(ish) to design and code a game to show off at the end of the jam. At the beginning of each Scarlet Game Jam, we will also be unveiling the (optional) theme to inspire or challenge our participants, which changes with every Scarlet Game Jam, so each year is a new experience! Programmers, musicians, and artists are welcome, but no experience is necessary! Check out our website for more information: (TBD). This time around, the game jam is 2 weeks long to give everyone extra time to work on their games! Feel free to take the whole 2 weeks, one week, or even a single day to work on your game. Join the COGS Discord here! Any announcements about the jam will be blasted here: https://cogs.club/discord Make sure to sign up on our website to ensure free food for the in-person closing ceremony on April 14th. Schedule: TBD
name: Scarlet Game Jam Fall 2024
